SKILL|hermes-agent-recovery|"Recover a broken Hermes Agent — dead SSH backends, config deadlocks, and blocked tools. Use when all filesystem/terminal tools fail due to a terminal backend misconfiguration."
STEP|1|ALL tools (terminal, read_file, write_file, patch, search_files, execute_code) fail with the same backend error
STEP|2|Error pattern: `SSH connection failed: Permission denied`, `Docker daemon not running`, etc.
STEP|3|System prompt shows `Terminal backend: ssh` (or docker/modal/…) with a probe timeout
STEP|4|Verify it's a backend deadlock, not a single-command failure:
STEP|5|Check the config indirectly — if you have `skill_manage`, you can create a skill and its files ARE written locally:
STEP|6|`skill_manage` writes to the Hermes HOST filesystem locally — use this as a scratchpad
STEP|7|`memory` — capture findings for the user to act on
STEP|8|`browser_navigate` — can read docs from hermes-agent.nousresearch.com
STEP|9|The user running `hermes config set terminal.backend local` on the Hermes host
STEP|10|**Don't assume `skill_manage` writes through the terminal backend.** It writes locally to `~/.hermes/skills/` on the Hermes host, bypassing SSH/Docker/Modal.
STEP|11|**Don't try 15 different approaches before telling the user.** If skill_manage works locally, you've confirmed the deadlock. Tell the user immediately.
STEP|12|**Don't attempt to edit config.yaml programmatically.** The security guard will refuse with "Agent cannot modify security-sensitive configuration."
STEP|13|**cronjob scripts must be in `~/.hermes/scripts/`** — you can't place them there from a deadlocked session. Skip this path.
STEP|14|`references/ssh-deadlock-error.md` — Full SSH error transcript, affected/unaffected tool list, security guard message
PIT|**Don't assume `skill_manage` writes through the terminal backend.** It writes locally to `~/.hermes/skills/` on the Hermes host, bypassing SSH/Docker/Modal.
PIT|**Don't try 15 different approaches before telling the user.** If skill_manage works locally, you've confirmed the deadlock. Tell the user immediately.
PIT|**Don't attempt to edit config.yaml programmatically.** The security guard will refuse with "Agent cannot modify security-sensitive configuration."
PIT|**cronjob scripts must be in `~/.hermes/scripts/`** — you can't place them there from a deadlocked session. Skip this path.